OL,3,CGovernment ordered to hold public
OL,4,Cinquiry into murder of GAA official
OL,5,CSean Brown
OL,7,FIn September, the Government said it
OL,8,Fwould not order a public inquiry into
OL,9,Fthe abduction and killing of the 61-
OL,10,Fyear-old who was ambushed as he locked
OL,11,Fthe gates at Bellaghy Wolfe Tones Club
OL,12,Fin Co Londonderry in May 1997.
OL,14,FNo-one has ever been convicted of his
OL,15,Fmurder.
OL,17,FHis widow, Bridie, brought judicial
OL,18,Freview proceedings challenging the
OL,19,Flegality of the decision by the
OL,20,FNorthern Ireland Secretary not to hold
OL,21,Fan inquiry.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/10
