OL,3,CGovernment ordered to hold public
OL,4,Cinquiry into murder of GAA official
OL,5,CSean Brown
OL,7,F"No viable alternative to a public
OL,8,Finquiry has been advanced. In these
OL,9,Fcircumstances, there can be only one
OL,10,Flawful answer, a public inquiry must
OL,11,Fbe convened to satisfy the State's
OL,12,FArticle 2 obligation.
OL,14,F"I therefore make an order of mandamus
OL,15,Fcompelling the Secretary of State for
OL,16,FNorthern Ireland (Hilary Benn) to
OL,17,Fcause a public inquiry to be held
OL,18,Funder the Inquiries Act 2005 into the
OL,19,Fdeath of Sean Brown on the 12th of
OL,20,FMay, 1997."
