OL,7,F"However, the agencies of the State
OL,8,Fput their face against the interests
OL,9,Fof justice and frustrated access to
OL,10,Fjustice for this family and today is
OL,11,Fthe inevitable consequences of that."
OL,13,FEarlier this year, a coroner said his
OL,14,Fability to examine the death of Mr
OL,15,FBrown had been "compromised" by the
OL,16,Fextent of confidential State material
OL,17,Fbeing excluded from the proceedings on
OL,18,Fnational security grounds.
